job_description:
Position: Data Developer (Business Intelligence) - Hybrid Working Model ( 3 days per week in Blainville, QC)
Location: Blainville

YOUR CHALLENGE You will be responsible for designing, developing, and optimizing data management and data processing solutions within the Microsoft Azure environment;
You will ensure the ingestion, transformation, and availability of data to support the organization’s analytical, operational, and decision‑making needs;
You will play a key role in implementing robust, reliable, scalable, and secure data architectures. YOUR RESPONSIBILITES Collect and integrate data from internal and external sources, both structured and unstructured (JSON, CSV, XML, Parquet), primarily using Azure Data Factory and native Azure connectors;
Transform, clean, and standardize data to ensure quality, consistency, and compliance with organizational standards;
Design, develop, and maintain reliable, automated, and resilient data pipelines;
Use analytical services such as Azure Synapse Analytics to query, process, and analyze large data volumes;
Monitor the performance of pipelines, processing workloads, and data environments. YOUR SPECIFIC SUCCESS MEASURES Provide recommendations quickly and effectively;
Successfully complete data updates and migrations;
Ensure data quality using KPIs. WHAT WE ARE LOOKING FOR Bachelor’s degree in computer science, Data Science, Information Systems, or a related field;
Minimum of 3 years of experience as Data Developer with Azure Cloud technologies, Apache Spark, and Python;
Hands‑on experience with Azure Synapse, Azure Event Hubs, Serverless SQL Pool, ADF Data Pipeline, ETL, Logic Apps, and Power BI.

Experience with SQL, No

SQL, SQL Server, and Delta Lake;
Demonstrated analytical and problem‑solving skills;
Knowledge of CI/CD pipelines using Azure Dev Ops;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
Ability to succeed in a fast‑paced environment;
Bilingualism (written and spoken).
